Crown Point first appeared on the 1990 U.S. Census as a census-designated place (CDP).

As of the [[census]]<ref name="GR2">{{cite web |url=https://www.census.gov |publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]] |accessdate=January 31, 2008 |title=U.S. Census website }}</ref> of 2000, there were 75 people, 28 households, and 19 families residing in the CDP. The population density was {{convert|21.1|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. There were 38 housing units at an average density of {{convert|10.7|/sqmi|/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of the CDP was 88.00% [[Race (United States Census)|White]], 4.00% [[Race (United States Census)|Native American]], 1.33% [[Race (United States Census)|Asian]], 1.33% from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 5.33% from two or more races. 2.67% of the population were [[Race (United States Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Race (United States Census)|Latino]] of any race.

There were 28 households, out of which 32.1% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 60.7% were [[Marriage|married couples]] living together, 3.6% had a female householder with no husband present, and 32.1% were non-families. 28.6% of all households were made up of individuals, and 10.7% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 2.43 and the average family size was 2.95.

In the CDP, the population was spread out, with 21.3% under the age of 18, 5.3% from 18 to 24, 28.0% from 25 to 44, 36.0% from 45 to 64, and 9.3% who were 65 years of age or older. The median age was 42 years. For every 100 females, there were 97.4 males. For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 126.9 males.

The median income for a household in the CDP was $59,063, and the median income for a family was $59,063. Males had a median income of $36,250 versus $41,250 for females. The [[per capita income]] for the CDP was $17,498. There were no families and 15.6% of the population living below the [[poverty line]], including no under eighteens and 100.0% of those over 64.

